SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1140
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor Claire Yi upon winning the 2025-2026
Tennessee Association of School Librarians
Bookmark Contest.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
young Tennesseans who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as
emerging leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary young person is Claire Yi, who recently won the 2025-
2026 Tennessee Association of School Librarians Bookmark Contest; and
WHEREAS, Claire Yi is the second student from Tusculum View Elementary School to
win the contest and one of more than 100 entrants who submitted an original design for the
bookmark contest, which had as its theme "Color Your World Through Books at Your School
Library"; and
WHEREAS, the designs were judged according to creativity, commitment to the year's
theme, and material usage, and Ms. Yi, competing successfully in the intermediate division,
secured first-place honors; and
WHEREAS, the intellectual aptitude, ambition, and character displayed by Claire Yi
surely bode well for her future success; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Yi's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize and honor Claire Yi upon winning the
2025-2026 Tennessee Association of School Librarians Bookmark Contest and wish her all the
best in her future endeavors.
